# CSS Styling Guidelines

## BEM Methodology with Databricks Prefix

### 1. Class Naming Convention
- **Block**: `.db-component-name` (base component class)
- **Element**: `.db-component-name__element` (child elements)
- **Modifier**: `.db-component-name--modifier` (variant/state classes)

### 2. Required Base Structure
```css
.db-component-name {
  /* Base component styles */
}

.db-component-name__element {
  /* Child element styles */
}

.db-component-name--variant {
  /* Variant modifier styles */
}

.db-component-name--state {
  /* State modifier styles (disabled, loading, etc.) */
}
```

### 3. Design Token Usage
Reference design tokens from [src/tokens](mdc:src/tokens/index.ts):
- Use CSS custom properties for token values
- Prefer token values over hardcoded values for:
  - Colors (primary, secondary, text, background)
  - Spacing (margins, padding)
  - Typography (font-size, line-height, font-weight)
  - Border radius, shadows, transitions

### 4. Responsive Design
- Use token-based breakpoints for media queries
- Mobile-first approach when needed
- Consider component scalability across viewport sizes

### 5. Accessibility Considerations
- Ensure adequate color contrast ratios
- Support focus indicators
- Consider reduced motion preferences
- Use semantic color names, not visual descriptions

### 6. Component State Styling
- Support `:hover`, `:focus`, `:active` states
- Handle `disabled` state appropriately
- Consider loading/pending states where applicable